title: Girls soccer: Galena downs Carson
text:
Girls soccer: Galena downs Carson Jim Krajewski , jkrajewski@rgj.com 10:06 p.m. PDT October 20, 2015 Buy Photo Carson's Valerie Sue Meyer, left, and Galena's Hannah Haase chase down the ball during Tuesday's game at Galena. (Photo: Andy Barron) Buy Photo CONNECT 4 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
As the girls soccer season winds down, Galena is rounding into playoff shape 
Galena scored early, then added a goal late, and held on to take a 2-1 win over Carson on Tuesday at Galena. 
Mackenzie Reynolds scored first for the Grizzlies, in the first few minutes of the game. The Senators attacked furiously through much of the rest of the match, controlling the ball and tempo and the ball, but was no table to convert thanks to Galenaâ€™s stifling defense.
